Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 110, 19 Name Athanodotos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 169.15.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0915)
